cast.text:
Hey, Farcaster Friends!! I've joined the GiGiFIT Acceptance Challenge in order to help raise money for our local GiGis Playhouse!

What is GiGis? It's a Down syndrome achievement center that offers 100% FREE programs for individuals with Down syndrome. They have locations all over the United States and in Mexico!

We have so so greatly benefited from GiGis and it's truly our second home. We are there 3, 4 sometimes 5 days a week for things like music classes or speech therapy!!

If you'd like to join our team (even if you can't join in person) or donate I've left a link here! 

https://support.gigisplayhouse.org/gigifit-acceptance-challenge-2025/team/the-fox-files?participant=madison-sommer

html.ogTitle: GiGiFIT Acceptance Challenge 2025 - The foX Files
html.ogDescription: You have the power to help us create a more accepting world for all.  Will you step up to the challenge?        My fundraising team is taking part in the GiGiFIT Acceptance Challenge because we wholeheartedly believe in GiGiâ€™s Playhouse and its mission of sending a global message of acceptance for all. Join us in championing GiGiâ€™s mission by joining our team, contributing to our page, or sharing our powerful message of acceptance with your friends.  The Acceptance Challenge isn't just about making a donation or attending an event; it's about sparking a revolution. Let's rise up together and declare, â€œWe will not accept our family and friends being seen as less than or secondary!â€ It's crucial that everyone recognizes the importance of this physical and social movement for acceptanceâ€”a movement that seeks the betterment of those who inspire us the most. Let's unite our voices to amplify the acceptance and inclusion of a population that has been silenced for far too long. Together we can create a world where our loved ones aren't subjected to bullying, isolation, or being left behind simply because of a diagnosis. Will you MOVE for acceptance??

text:
A story in 2 parts.

Spring back door cold front puts the chill into coastal Massachusetts this weekend.

Many such cases; and exhibit A for a solid reason why we choose to deploy heaps of row cover on the farm in the spring.

We just donâ€™t warm up very fast and every crop we have trialed had benefited from roe cover in April and early May.

The row cover a) protects the crops from the coldest nights b) reduces early season wind stress which allows us to skip hardening off most crops c) prevents pest pressure - helpful when you donâ€™t use pesticides d) elevated soil temperature, which increases biological activity which starts the flywheel of soil feeding crop feeding soil = will accelerate harvest dates by 2-3 weeks for many spring crops.

Can be a struggle in the wind, this AM wasnâ€™t too bad all things considered.  These are our early alliums - scallions and onions â€¦ the scallions will be ready early June, onions early July.  Covers will stay on til sometime in May.  Weâ€™ll open them up to cultivate
